{
  "texts": [
    "However, deriving these suffixes through gradientbased searching is computationally inefficient.",
    "The exponentially increasing search space of random suffixes with length expansion presents significant challenges to search efficiency.",
    "Besides, the random initialization for each search is inefficient, incurring additional but unnecessary searching costs.",
    "Recent work (Zou et al., 2023) suggests that the adversarial suffixes may possess universal transferability across models, indicating that the previously searched suffix could serve as an effective initialization.",
    "Furthermore, Meade et al. (2024) finds that models aligned through preference optimization exhibit robustness against suffix transfer."
  ]
}